00:00:01.610 --> 00:00:04.320
General product management skills are

00:00:04.320 --> 00:00:08.085
foundational to becoming an excellent data Product Manager.

00:00:08.085 --> 00:00:12.180
You'll need to be constantly talking to users or potential users of

00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:16.290
different personas and segments in order to understand their pain points.

00:00:16.290 --> 00:00:18.120
As you learn from this course,

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:22.605
you'll need to be adept at analyzing data to understand trends at large,

00:00:22.605 --> 00:00:26.970
measure their success of and iterate on your experiments, features and products,

00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:29.205
setting KPIs rally teams,

00:00:29.205 --> 00:00:33.770
and to build our experiences powered by automated data processing and serving.

00:00:33.770 --> 00:00:36.410
You'll need to work cross-functionally with teams ranging

00:00:36.410 --> 00:00:38.810
from engineers and designers to come up with

00:00:38.810 --> 00:00:42.110
high-level solutions that meet user's needs or being

00:00:42.110 --> 00:00:46.300
technically feasible in terms of engineering resources and capabilities.

00:00:46.300 --> 00:00:51.260
You'll need to prioritize development of the features and products based on user impact,

00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:55.535
engineering feasibility, market timing in business alignment.

00:00:55.535 --> 00:01:00.050
Then you'll packages prioritization into a strategic roadmap in order to

00:01:00.050 --> 00:01:02.090
evangelize and justify to

00:01:02.090 --> 00:01:05.855
internal stakeholders on why we're building what we're building.

00:01:05.855 --> 00:01:08.389
You'll need to work with a team in facilitating

00:01:08.389 --> 00:01:12.170
the development process from writing specs, user stories,

00:01:12.170 --> 00:01:15.005
feature requirements, setting milestones,

00:01:15.005 --> 00:01:18.965
identifying edge cases and setting acceptance criteria.

00:01:18.965 --> 00:01:21.545
You'll need to work with marketing, editorial,

00:01:21.545 --> 00:01:26.750
and technical writing teams to prepare large communication's collateral from blog posts,

00:01:26.750 --> 00:01:31.890
documentation in product messaging and copy and press releases.

